00:00:09.309 --> 00:00:10.309
BUILD IT

00:00:10.309 --> 00:00:13.990
Michael Grab assembles sculptures out of rocks
using only gravity.

00:00:13.990 --> 00:00:18.570
They’re meant to evoke awe and disbelief
surrounding the forces of nature, as well

00:00:18.570 --> 00:00:22.140
as illustrate what can be accomplished with
delicacy and patience.

00:00:22.140 --> 00:00:26.900
The series is called Gravity Glue, and you
can watch him assemble the zen garden-like

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:29.189
projects on his YouTube channel.

00:00:29.189 --> 00:00:33.080
Shinri Tezuka sculpts intricate animals that
are also lollipops.

00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:38.400
Amezaiku is a traditional art from Japan in
which heated taffy is sculpted with tweezers

00:00:38.400 --> 00:00:40.260
and scissors and then painted.

00:00:40.260 --> 00:00:44.800
The taffy cools within minutes so each piece
must be crafted as efficiently as possible.

00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:50.580
Tezuka is the only amezaiku artist in Japan
who uses gradation to color his candy but

00:00:50.580 --> 00:01:03.520
he holds classes to teach others his unique
style.

00:01:03.520 --> 00:01:07.490
Anish Kapoor built an endlessly churning whirlpool.

00:01:07.490 --> 00:01:12.280
The project is called Descension and is meant
to evoke the feelings of discomfort we experience

00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:14.990
when confronted with empty spaces.

00:01:14.990 --> 00:01:19.780
The first iteration of the project was installed
in India, but in May another one was built

00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:22.439
in an abandoned Italian movie theater.

00:01:22.439 --> 00:01:26.720
Veronica Richterova repurposes plastic bottles
into plants.

00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:31.549
She heats bottles up, carves and attaches
them to other bottles in order to create everything

00:01:31.549 --> 00:01:34.920
from colorful cacti to intricate chandeliers.

00:01:34.920 --> 00:01:39.850
She has a fascination with plastic, and not
only collects it, but also has written extensively

00:01:39.850 --> 00:01:41.799
on its history and usage.

00:01:41.799 --> 00:01:47.299
Asuka Dori builds transformer toys out of
candy boxes which is just really cool.

00:01:47.299 --> 00:01:53.100
&nbsp;Here’s a caramel box that turns into a
robot, and this horse turns into a tank.

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:54.100
DRAW IT

00:01:54.100 --> 00:01:59.729
David Spriggs creates 3D images by layering
sheets of engraved or painted glass.

00:01:59.729 --> 00:02:04.340
This piece titled the sun king, depicts a
police officer in riot gear and is based off

00:02:04.340 --> 00:02:08.110
of a Roman statue destroyed during the French
revolution.

00:02:08.110 --> 00:02:13.209
Spriggs is interested in the relationship
between state power and its faceless enforcers,

00:02:13.209 --> 00:02:18.420
which is why the subject is 20 feet tall,
and its face is obscure from every angle.

00:02:18.420 --> 00:02:22.260
Xavier paints the desert with light using
light up cacti.

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:27.490
He wanted to create an uncontrollable and
erratic world and then let the viewers interpret

00:02:27.490 --> 00:02:30.280
their own personal narrative as they watched
the film.

00:02:30.280 --> 00:02:46.640
Find the link below to watch the whole incredible
video.

00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:56.560
And now for the organic, globular surrealist
artwork of Jung-Yeon Min.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:03:03.230
PLAY IT

00:03:03.230 --> 00:03:06.890
Len Solomon is an inventor as well as a one
man orchestra.

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:12.540
He built his majestic bellowphone in 1983,
and it’s comprised of playground balls,

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:23.930
coat hanger wire, vacuum parts and plumbing
pipes.

00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:29.730
Dance crews unite to form AXYZM, a company
that specializes in movement design.

00:03:29.730 --> 00:03:40.650
Here’s their first video which combines
body movement, props and patterns.

00:03:40.650 --> 00:03:52.709
Together Or Alone by Eternal Summers features
stop motion using found objects directed by

00:03:52.709 --> 00:04:16.940
Japhy Riddle.

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:18.579
Inspiration also comes from you.

00:04:18.579 --> 00:04:20.900
